               <desc type="building-data" xml:lang="en"> 
                  <p source="#bibl000048i-1">Located at the north end of the small complex’s central axis, the great hall of the Shrine to the Eastern Peak is 12 x 9.9 meters and three bays wide. It is crowned with an overhanging gable (xuanshan 懸山) roof. The god of the Eastern Peak is worshiped inside the hall (Liu 1986, 29; Liu et al., 2015, vol. 7, 1).</p>    
